{"ECBALLIUM":[{"def":"A genus of cucurbitaceous plants consisting of the single species Ecballium agreste (or Elaterium), the squirting cucumber.","pos":""}],"ECBASIS":[{"def":"A figure in which the orator treats of things according to their events consequences.","pos":""}],"ECBATIC":[{"def":"Denoting a mere result or consequence, as distinguished from telic, which denotes intention or purpose; thus the phrase so that it was fulfilled,\" is ecbatic; if rendered \"in order that it might be.","pos":""}],"ECBOLE":[{"def":"A digression in which a person is introduced speaking his own words.","pos":""}],"ECBOLIC":[{"def":"A drug, as ergot, which by exciting uterine contractions promotes the expulsion of the contents of the uterus.","pos":""}],"ECBOLINE":[{"def":"An alkaloid constituting the active principle of ergot; -- so named from its power of producing abortion.","pos":""}]}